    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p>politeness of</p>
			<p><persName role="author">Mr A Dovale</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cura√ßao</placeName> <date>9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Novr 1849</date></p>
			<p>To the</p>
			<p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">You will oblige<lb/> me by adding the small amot. of<lb/> three dollars which will be herewith<lb/> handed to you by <persName>Mr A Dovale</persName><lb/> of this <placeName>Island</placeName> to the subscriptions<lb/> for the relief of our distressed brethren<lb/> in <placeName>Palestine</placeName>&#44; I regret that I am<lb/> not possessed of sufficient influence<lb/> here to collect for so sacred a purpose<lb/> and one which ought to interest and influence<lb/> every Child of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#8212;As soon as<lb/> I can find time I will send a longer<lb/> letter in the meantime accept the<lb/> kind wishes and regards of yours<lb/> faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author"><add>&#63;</add> Nathan</persName></p>
			<p>PS&#8212;Will you have the kindness<lb/> to request <persName>Mr Bush</persName> to send me books<lb/> which I have ordered <persName role="author">AN</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(11)">Turn over</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>24 Kesvan 5610</date></p>
			<p>A daughter of <placeName>Israel</placeName> has added &#36;3.00</p>
			<p>A son of <placeName>Israel</placeName> ....... 1.00</p>
			<p>another ...... 1.00</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> the <date>11 Dec 1849</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I have recd from <persName>Mr.<lb/> Nathan</persName> a small amt. to hand<lb/> to you&#44; but not knowing who is<lb/> your agent in this city nor have<lb/> a sure hand to send it to you<lb/> I think much better to keep it<lb/> for you&#44; <sic>untill</sic> I receive your<lb/> advice. I remain dear Sir one<lb/> of your brothers who would feel<lb/> very happy at any time to render<lb/> you any services that I can with<lb/> pleasure.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">A. I. Dovale</hi></persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>158 St. South store</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>120 Chambers St. Residence</placeName>.</p>

          
        </body>
